CS 88 is a connector course for Data 8 (data8.org) that is designed for students who want a more complete introduction to Computer Science. This 2 unit course covers much of the material addressed in CS 61A, but with a data-centric perspective. Check out the course site for topics covered last semester (cs88-website.github.io).

CS 88 will have around 50 students in Fall, and labs will be on Monday afternoons from 11-1pm and 1-3pm. If you are interested in helping out, please fill out the linked form. This is a great way to get more involved with the growing data science program at UC Berkeley. The class is small and tight-knit, so you will get to know the students and instructors really well throughout the semester.

Students of any major who have taken CS 61A or CS 88 are welcome to apply!
